CYCLE=0
IDEA=$'Click-to-view tool output in the Mission Control dashboard\n\nOUTCOME\nMake the tool-event rows in an agent\'s message stream clickable. Clicking a\nrow like `Read (ok, 0.04s)` opens a modal showing the actual output that tool\nproduced. Today the dashboard only ships `args_summary` (redacted, 256B cap)\nand `error_summary`; the real tool output is observed by the PostToolUse hook\nand then discarded. Tool outputs are the highest-bandwidth observability signal\na coordinator has into what a teammate just did — "Read returned 0.04s" tells\nyou almost nothing; the file contents tell you everything. This closes a real\nblind spot in the coordinator-in-the-loop observability model, which is the\nproduct\'s moat.\n\nSHAPE (implementation direction — the planner should validate against the code)\n- Capture tool output at the `sdk_teammate.py` PostToolUse hook (where outputs\n  are currently seen and discarded).\n- Store outputs in a bounded, in-memory, per-teammate structure (~50 events\n  max, evicting oldest). Do NOT add output bodies to the frozen `ToolEvent`\n  dataclass and do NOT push them inline on every broker snapshot / WebSocket\n  state push — outputs are too large for that. Use a parallel store keyed by\n  (teammate_id, tool_use_id).\n- Serve via a new lazy-fetch HTTP endpoint on `ui_server.py`:\n  `GET /tool-output/<teammate_id>/<tool_use_id>`. Localhost-only bind, same\n  security posture as the just-shipped `/wait-messages` endpoint. Returns the\n  (redacted, truncated) output body for that one tool invocation on demand.\n- Dashboard render: make the tool-event row (the MiniMessage rows produced by\n  `_format_tool_event_body` in ui_server.py) clickable; clicking opens a\n  modal in the ConfigDetailPanel style showing the output body, with a\n  copy-to-clipboard control.\n\nSECURITY — THE CRUX (decision already made by the operator)\nThis is the FIRST time tool OUTPUT content crosses the broker boundary. Outputs\nare unbounded and can contain anything: shell stdout, file contents, web\nresponses — including secrets. The existing `redaction.py` is args-only and\nassumes a known small input shape per tool; it is NOT sufficient for outputs.\n- Redaction-failure policy: MASK matched secrets inline (e.g. `AKIA[REDACTED]`),\n  showing the surrounding non-secret text. Patterns to cover at minimum: AWS\n  access keys (`AKIA...`), OpenAI-style keys (`sk-...`), GitHub tokens\n  (`ghp_...`), bearer tokens, PEM private keys (`-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----`),\n  AWS session tokens. FAIL LOUD (emit a clear marker line, never silently pass\n  raw) if the redactor itself raises.\n- Hard truncation cap on stored/served output (~4KB suggested).\n- A redaction bug here is a credential leak. The redaction patterns must be\n  tested hard (happy + sad), and a sentinel security pass is mandatory before\n  merge.\n\nVALIDATION EXPECTATION\nTests at two layers (capture/redaction logic AND the HTTP endpoint), happy and\nsad paths at each, per the project\'s validate-before-change standard. Redaction\npattern coverage is the highest-priority test surface.\n\nEXPLICITLY OUT OF SCOPE (do not plan these)\n- Persistent on-disk JSONL of tool outputs (a separate, larger feature).\n- Syntax highlighting of output bodies.\n- Diff view between outputs.\n- Any change to how `args_summary` / `error_summary` already work.\n\nCONTEXT POINTERS FOR THE PLANNER\n- `claude_crew/sdk_teammate.py` — PostToolUse hook (F8 tool tracking) is where\n  output is currently seen and dropped.\n- `claude_crew/teammate.py` — `ToolEvent` dataclass and the `_completed_tool_events`\n  deque; understand why ToolEvent is frozen/small before deciding the store shape.\n- `claude_crew/redaction.py` — existing args-only redaction (v1 allowlist:\n  Bash, Task, WebFetch); the output redactor is new work alongside it.\n- `claude_crew/ui_server.py` — `_format_tool_event_body`, the existing route\n  registration in `_make_app`, and the localhost-bind posture in `serve()`; the\n  `/wait-messages` endpoint added in the most recent feature is the reference\n  pattern for a new localhost HTTP route.\n- `claude_crew/broker.py` — `BrokerSnapshot` / `snapshot()` and how tool_events\n  flow to the UI today.\n- `claude_crew/ui/dashboard.html` — the dashboard front-end (MiniMessage rows,\n  ConfigDetailPanel modal style to mirror).\n- CLAUDE.md "validate the whole suite when changing widely-consumed behavior" —\n  run the full `uv run pytest`, not a filtered subset, at the validation gate.'
